tip.text: The poached egg special with coconut rice, spinach and cashew nuts was good! Reasonable for £10, perfect for lunch
Tasty cheap Gyoza, with rice makes it a filling lunch. Good spot in the market
Quiche and as much salad as you can fit on the plate for £5. Great bargain and perfect sunny spot outside to enjoy it.
Bife de chorizo a Las Cabras was huge. I couldn't finish it, lots of delicious sides to accompany the steak that was cooked well. Super busy restaurant so arrive early or you will have to wait
Healthy and good food, although bland and lacking flavour. My plate needed some herbs and seasoning. Good friendly service though
It's good, not great. The burger wasnt juicy, slightly dry and the bread should be better, It's cheap so you get what you pay for. I've had better burgers. Didn't live up to the hype.

formattedAddress: Jorge Luis Borges 1766 (e/ Russel & Costa Rica)

tip.text: Spaghetti 🍝 was delicious. Simple and perfect. Service with a smile and we both practiced our Spanish and English respectively. Muy beuno
Mooi Salad is good and its large. Perfect for lunch to keep you going. Indifferent service. It looked like an effort to be served.
Great 1960's house a short walk to the beach. Plenty of restaurants nearby and much nicer than central Montevideo. Stay here it's great
Double cheeseburger was the perfect hangover cure! Juicy and delicious. Go for it with everything and you won't be disappointed!
Great steak and efficient service. Sit at the bar for a good view of everybody working and your steak being cooked. It is EXPENSIVE as it's next to the cruise ship dock, but I enjoyed my meal
Amazing steak with great service. An English menu is available, ribeye was cooked perfectly, muy jugoso - rare
Great pool hat overlooks Salta. Easy 15min walk into the center of town for many options for lunch and dinner if you don't want to eat at the hotel. Food here was good also.
Ceviche was unbelievably good! So fresh and the perfect hit of chili. The mixed salad was huge and was too much to finish. Great food I loved it.
Friendly staff in a beautiful old house. The room was spotless and there was always someone around to help with dinner, taxis or some advice on Corrientes. The flooring is unbelievably good!
Amazing food, amazing atmosphere. This place feels intimate and at someone's home. The live music adds to this truly authentic restaurant. It's out of town but worth the taxi ride.
Fresh vegetables at last and they were delicious. I'm staying longer in Salta and Chirimoya is one of the reasons. I am not vegetarian but if I was given this everyday I would be! 👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻
Lorca is amazing. Finally some food that has flavour in Argentina. The service is great and perfectly accommodating my lack of Spanish. The cheap house wine is very good! 👌🏻
Breakfast And juices are great
Everything! Perfect Thai food and it's super cheap. Great lunch spot!
Everything, great Thai food and friendly service
Great food, Amazing Service and Perfect Atmosphere! Cannot rate highly enough

formattedAddress: rue Courbin (rue Pont de la Mousque)

tip.text: Chicken Karaage and Tonkotsu every time! Delicious and the my make some mean cocktails from their amazingly well stocked bar. Even better that I live round the corner
Cocktails and service are PERFECT! The corpse reviver is actually worth dying for.
The food is unbelievably good! Pork and ginger rolls are to die for and the chicken Karaage is the best I have ever had!
Service was great and the food was inventive and delicious. I would highly recommend the sharing menu where they just serve up there best dishes of the day!
The view is great, the service is atrocious! Repeated requests for menus , drinks that never arrived and some of my food was dropped on the floor by the waitress. Very poor service I will not return
Nice coffee in an old shop house. The cakes looked amazing.
Delicious Khmer food. Extensive menu and tasty
Sunsets and the warm shallow clear ocean

Good beach area with loungers and attentive staff. Always cleaning and checking on the guests. Good healthy food although lacking in Khmer options. Purely generic international food although it's good
Nice pastries and a large upstairs seating area looking out over the river
Good view and pool. The barstaff are great and will make you any cocktail or drink you require. The Negronis they made for me were excellent!
Everything I have had here is great. The coffees are excellent and the food is delicious. The service is slow but that's due to their popularity, bring a book sit back and relax, it's worth the wait!

location.state: จังหวัดสตูล
formattedAddress: จังหวัดสตูล

tip.text: Everything I ate! The sushi was great. Perfectly made and amazingly presented. The tempura was light and crispy and the homemade udon were delicious. The staff are super knowledgable
Squid with dried chili and Kangkong was tasty. I ate every last bit!

formattedAddress: Lot 1698 Pantai Tenga (in Holiday Villa Langkawi)

tip.text: Great rooms providing everything you need. It's a short walk to the beautiful beach yet this place has its own private pool. Perfect. What more do you require????
Ice skating on Christmas Eve was magical. Made me feel very festive, the champagne afterwards helped no end!
Great service. Friendly staff and knowledgable with quick service. The sunset was killer
Loads of food options and it's a great environment for a night out with friends. It can be rather expensive so choose wisely what you eat.
Nasi goreng was delicious and the Merlot went well with it
Great cocktails and THAT view
Free drinks and nibbles between 5-7pm and with that view, what is not to like!
Dirty Beans and Baked Eggs is EPIC!!! I will definitely be coming back and having it again.
